  <p>During 2019, the construction industry developed under a scenario of low application of federal resources
    for the acquisition of new housing, accompanied by unclear rules for the operation. However, 2020 begins
    revitalized due to the publication of the activity parameters that will be followed by CONAVI, oriented to
    the attention of the population with greater lag in this matter.   2019 for the construction industry was
    marked by the lower allocation of federal resources to encourage the acquisition of new housing, in addition
    to the delay in the issuance of the National Housing Plan. Nevertheless, 2020 began on a strong footing driven
    by the publication of the latter, which is aimed to attend the underserved population in this matter.</p>

  <p>Likewise, the President of Mexico announced the allocation of more than MXN 200,000 million to stimulate
    the sector; while Infonavit and Fovissste are launching new financing schemes, such as the capability of
    joining credits from both institutions, actions which together will strengthen the industry in order to
    achieve a greater dynamism.</p>

